potential disciplinary action

00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:09.230
and feel a whole lot better
in the process.

00:01:11.140 --> 00:01:14.220
The first step to understanding
Information Security

00:01:14.220 --> 00:01:15.820
is being able to define it.

00:01:16.510 --> 00:01:20.250
Information Security
or "InfoSec", relates to the steps

00:01:20.250 --> 00:01:23.380
we take to protect electronic
and physical information,

00:01:23.380 --> 00:01:26.390
as well as ensure the integrity
of our technology systems.

00:01:27.300 --> 00:01:29.930
Consider for a minute just
how much sensitive information

00:01:29.930 --> 00:01:31.650
we have on our systems -

00:01:31.650 --> 00:01:34.380
like financial details,
health information,

00:01:34.380 --> 00:01:37.810
personally identifiable
information, trade secrets,

00:01:37.810 --> 00:01:39.410
and other
intellectual property.

00:01:40.460 --> 00:01:42.780
Without security
measures, our organization

00:01:42.780 --> 00:01:44.950
becomes vulnerable
to data breaches

00:01:44.950 --> 00:01:48.430
where unauthorized people
can access, modify, disclose

00:01:48.430 --> 00:01:50.550
or even destroy
our valuable information.

00:01:51.650 --> 00:01:52.880
Once we understand

00:01:52.880 --> 00:01:55.090
the definition
of Information Security,

00:01:55.090 --> 00:01:56.450
the next step is to be alert

00:01:56.450 --> 00:01:59.300
to those trying to compromise
our systems and data.

00:01:59.300 --> 00:02:01.670
Examples include
"social engineers"

00:02:01.670 --> 00:02:03.340
who are people
trying to manipulate us

00:02:03.340 --> 00:02:05.720
into divulging
confidential information

00:02:05.720 --> 00:02:08.080
or allowing unauthorized
access to our systems.

00:02:08.910 --> 00:02:10.800
This could be a caller
pretending to be someone

00:02:10.800 --> 00:02:12.240
in a position of authority

00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:14.670
or someone you think you should
trust sending you an email

00:02:14.670 --> 00:02:16.719
encouraging you
to download new software.

00:02:17.510 --> 00:02:20.240
In the latter situation
this "phishing" email

00:02:20.240 --> 00:02:22.180
may contain downloads
and links infected

00:02:22.180 --> 00:02:25.970
with what’s called "malware",
like viruses and trojans,

00:02:25.970 --> 00:02:27.910
maliciously designed
to gather usernames

00:02:27.910 --> 00:02:30.390
and passwords, destroy content,

00:02:30.390 --> 00:02:33.480
steal trade secrets,
or even lock systems for ransom.

00:02:34.840 --> 00:02:37.700
We should always be alert to
anyone attempting to gain access

00:02:37.700 --> 00:02:39.300
to our system or facilities.

00:02:39.820 --> 00:02:42.730
Even when our devices are locked,
an experienced hacker

00:02:42.730 --> 00:02:45.880
can enter systems if they have
physical access and enough time.

00:02:46.910 --> 00:02:49.380
Be sure to contact
building security immediately

00:02:49.380 --> 00:02:52.940
if you notice any person, whether
an employee or a stranger,

00:02:52.940 --> 00:02:54.540
in any unauthorized area.

00:02:55.740 --> 00:02:58.540
Finally, to ensure information
security,

00:02:58.540 --> 00:03:01.540
we all must TAKE SPECIFIC
PRECAUTIONS such as:

00:03:01.540 --> 00:03:03.530
Make timely system updates
and routinely

00:03:03.530 --> 00:03:05.780
run pre-approved
anti-virus applications

00:03:05.780 --> 00:03:07.590
as instructed by
our IT department.

00:03:08.370 --> 00:03:10.480
Only download items
from trusted sources.

00:03:11.560 --> 00:03:13.860
Lock computer, laptop
and phone screens

00:03:13.860 --> 00:03:15.460
when they are not in use.

00:03:16.040 --> 00:03:18.770
Always create unique passwords
that are easy to remember

00:03:18.770 --> 00:03:20.570
but difficult
for others to guess,

00:03:20.570 --> 00:03:23.380
incorporating a variety
of lower and uppercase letters,

00:03:23.380 --> 00:03:26.060
numbers and symbols,
with at least eight characters.

00:03:27.340 --> 00:03:29.470
Never give your passwords
to anyone without first

00:03:29.470 --> 00:03:31.170
consulting with our
IT Department.

00:03:31.950 --> 00:03:34.720
Never leave devices unattended
or in public view

00:03:34.720 --> 00:03:37.370
and report instances of theft
to IT immediately.

00:03:38.700 --> 00:03:41.260
Never send confidential
information via email

00:03:41.260 --> 00:03:43.030
or instant message.

00:03:43.030 --> 00:03:46.040
Always use Virtual Private
Networking or VPN

00:03:46.550 --> 00:03:50.050
instead of using any unsecure or
possibly dangerous public Wi-Fi.

00:03:51.380 --> 00:03:55.000
And of course, immediately
report any suspected data breach

00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:58.380
to our IT, security,
or compliance departments,

00:03:58.380 --> 00:04:00.880
no matter how insignificant
you think it might be.

00:04:01.890 --> 00:04:04.380
In summary, the key
is to understand

00:04:04.380 --> 00:04:06.510
what information security is.

00:04:06.510 --> 00:04:09.180
Stay alert to those trying
to breach our systems

00:04:09.180 --> 00:04:10.830
and take all
of the safety precautions,

00:04:10.830 --> 00:04:12.430
outlined by our IT Department.

00:04:13.080 --> 00:04:16.230
Three simple steps to ensuring
information and system security.

