00:04:22.310 --> 00:04:23.660
it’s now probably pretty clear

00:04:23.660 --> 00:04:26.860
that you can’t provide your
credentials for the executive.

00:04:26.860 --> 00:04:29.540
In the short run, it may feel
like you didn’t help the team

00:04:29.540 --> 00:04:32.150
in a moment of need,
but in the long run,

00:04:32.150 --> 00:04:35.280
you’ll avoid the consequences
of violating company policy.

00:04:35.280 --> 00:04:37.920
Our information security
will remain strong,

00:04:37.920 --> 00:04:39.330
and your colleagues
will recognize

00:04:39.330 --> 00:04:41.610
that you are a person
who does the right thing,

00:04:41.610 --> 00:04:43.509
even when it seems
difficult to do so.

00:04:44.650 --> 00:04:46.999
Now, doesn’t that make you
feel better already?

